===============================================================================

EventBus has been installed!

The following file was created:
  config/initializers/event_bus.rb

This initializer contains:
  • EventBus configuration (timeouts, instrumentation, logging)
  • Middleware chain setup (logging, metrics, transaction tracking)
  • Documentation and examples for event handlers

Next steps:

1. Review and customize the configuration in config/initializers/event_bus.rb

2. Define your domain events:
   # app/events/orders/order_paid.rb
   class Orders::Events::OrderPaid
     attr_reader :order_id, :amount

     def initialize(order_id:, amount:)
       @order_id = order_id
       @amount = amount
     end

     def to_h
       { order_id: order_id, amount: amount }
     end

     def partition_key
       order_id
     end
   end

3. Create event handlers:
   # app/events/handlers/send_email_handler.rb
   class SendEmailHandler
     def call(event)
       OrderMailer.confirmation(event.order_id).deliver_later
     end
   end

4. Subscribe handlers in the initializer or pack-specific initializers:
   EventBus.subscribe(
     Orders::Events::OrderPaid,
     SendEmailHandler.new,
     priority: 8,
     async: false,
     error_strategy: :log
   )

5. Publish events in your application code:
   # In your service/controller
   EventBus.publish(Orders::Events::OrderPaid.new(order_id: 123, amount: 99.99))

Documentation:
  • GitHub: https://github.com/your-org/event_bus
  • README: https://github.com/your-org/event_bus#readme

